[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Apply a multiplier to just about every drop, reward and craft output in the game:[/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Multipliers[/b] — Resource (drops), Faith, Donation, Gratitude, Sin Shard, Happiness, Red/Green/Blue Tech Points. Every multiplier accepts 0.1–50, so you can reduce drops too, not just increase them.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Categories[/b] — nine toggles pick which item groups the Resource Multiplier touches:[/size]
[size=3]- Sticks (on by default)
- Crops: wheat, cabbage, carrot, beet, onion, lentils, pumpkin, hops, hemp, grapes, apples, berries, mushrooms, flowers, crop waste, hiccup grass (on)
- Seeds (off — they flood inventory fast)
- Logs: billets, planks, beams, flitches (on)
- Ores: iron, stone, marble, clay, coal, sulfur, silver/gold nuggets, graphite, diamond, sand, lifestone (on)
- Bugs: bee, butterfly, moth, maggot (on)
- Enemy Drops: bat wings, slime, jelly slugs (all colours), spider webs, bloody nails (on)
- Miscellaneous: honey, beeswax, ash, peat, salt, water, alcohol, chicken eggs, milk, metal scrap (off)
- Body Parts: blood, flesh, fat, skin, bone, skull (off)[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Craft Output Multiplier[/b] — scale the items produced by crafts. One log yields ×5 billets at the sawhorse if that's what you want. Optional per-station overrides (format: station_id=multi;station_id=multi). Progression crafts (tier upgrades, placements, repairs) and tools/weapons/armour are automatically excluded so progression isn't trivialised.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3]All multipliers apply the moment the mod loads — no perk or tech unlocks required. Set a value to 1 to leave a category vanilla; set 0.1 to reduce it instead of increasing.[/size]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/62]Where's Ma' Storage[/url] — one shared inventory. Essential if you're multiplying drops aggressively and don't want to juggle stockpile overflow manually.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/51]Auto-Loot Heavies[/url] — teleports timber/stone/marble/ore straight to stockpiles. Handles the extra drop volume without you walking back and forth.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/64]Gerry's Junk Trunk[/url] — sell off stockpile overflow automatically for cash.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/57]Queue Everything[/url] — queue large batches of crafts. Pairs well with a craft-output multiplier.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/65]FasterCraft Reloaded[/url] — speed up crafting. Multiplier × speed = finish big orders in minutes.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

